A N A C T
RELATING TO TOWNS AND CITIES -- RETIREMENT OF MUNICIPAL EMPLOYEES
Introduced By: Representatives Chippendale, Finkelman, Fascia, Newberry, Lima,
Noret, Nardone, Edwards, Paplauskas, and Hull
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: House Municipal Government & Housing
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 45-21-54 of the General Laws in Chapter 45-21 entitled "Retirement
2 of Municipal Employees" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 45-21-54. Reemployment of retired members.
4 Any retired member of the system is permitted to reenter the service of the system for not
5 more than seventy-five (75) ninety (90) working days in a calendar year without interruption of
6 pension benefits. Pension payments, however, are suspended when that period is exceeded. This
7 seventy-five-day (75) ninety (90) rule shall not apply to police officers, as defined in ยง 28-9.2-3,
8 for the purposes of their working private details, paid for by a nongovernmental entity. If the retired
9 member continues in service beyond the seventy-five-day (75) ninety (90) period (with his or her
10 annuity temporarily suspended) the member is not eligible for pension credit for the additional
11 service, nor is the member required to make pension contributions for this service; provided, that
12 any retired member of the system is permitted to serve as an elected city or town council member
13 or school committee member and continues to be eligible for and receive the retirement allowance
14 for service other than that as a council member or school committee member.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
